briefdescription.para: Enum for representing signal values for the BatteryChemistry signal.

detaileddescription.para: This enum maps each value in the signal's value table to a corresponding identifier. It is used to interpret the raw data received from the CAN bus and provides human-readable names for each value.

simplesect.para: Ensure the signal values are aligned with the data type and expected range of the signal.

briefdescription.para: Initializes the DbcStruct for CAN message processing.

detaileddescription.para: This function should be called before using the DbcStruct to ensure that all message structures are properly initialized. It sets up necessary memory and configurations.

st
Pointer to the DbcStruct instance that will be initialized.

briefdescription.para: Converts a physical value to its corresponding raw CAN value.

detaileddescription.para: This function takes a physical value and applies the scaling factor and offset specified in the Phys_Value_t structure to convert it to the raw CAN signal value. The raw value can then be transmitted in a CAN message.

phys_value
The physical value to be converted.
phys_struct
Pointer to the Phys_Value_t structure containing scaling and offset information.
The corresponding raw CAN value.
Converts a physical value to its corresponding raw CAN value.
This function converts a physical value (e.g., temperature) into a raw CAN signal value based on the scaling factor and offset stored in the Phys_Value_t structure.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the Phys_Value_t structure containing scaling factor and offset.

simplesect.para: The corresponding raw CAN signal value.

briefdescription.para: Converts a raw CAN value to its corresponding physical value.

detaileddescription.para: This function takes a raw CAN value and applies the scaling factor and offset specified in the Phys_Value_t structure to convert it to the physical signal value. The physical value represents the actual measured or calculated value of the signal.

raw_value
The raw CAN signal value to be converted.
phys_struct
Pointer to the Phys_Value_t structure containing scaling and offset information.
The corresponding physical value.
Converts a raw CAN value to its corresponding physical value.
